  "prompt": "How do I get a job in Singapore from India?",
  "response": "Here are steps to get a job in Singapore from India:\n\n1. Qualifications and Skills\n- Ensure you have relevant qualifications\n- Develop in-demand skills\n- Learn about Singapore's job market requirements\n\n2. Job Search Platforms\n- Use online job portals like:\n- JobsDB\n- LinkedIn\n- Monster Singapore\n- SGCareerJobs\n- Jobstreet\n- Company websites\n\n3. Work Visa Requirements\n- Obtain Employment Pass (EP)\n- Requires:\n- Job offer from Singaporean company\n- Min. monthly salary of S$4,500\n- Relevant qualifications/experience\n\n4. Networking\n- Connect on professional networking sites\n- Attend job fairs\n- Join professional groups\n- Use alumni networks\n\n5. Recruitment Agencies\n- Register with agencies specializing in Singapore placements\n- Examples: Michael Page, Robert Half\n\n6. Industry Focus\n- Tech\n- Finance\n- Engineering\n- Healthcare\n- Manufacturing\n\n7. Preparation\n- Update resume according to Singaporean format\n- Prepare for online/video interviews\n- Research potential employers\n- Understand local work culture\n\n8. Documentation\n- Valid passport\n- Educational certificates\n- Professional credentials\n- Work experience letters\n\nPersistence and strategic approach are key to success.",
